Pilonidal disease: 25 cases treated by the Dufourmentel technique.
 Twenty-five patients with pilonidal disease were treated by the Dufourmentel technique between 1984 and 1989.
 In this series, 18 patients (72 percent) were women and 7 (28 percent) were men (mean age, 24 years); hospital stay averaged 4 days.
 There were no recurrences and no reports of surgical wound infection.
 Diagnosis was confirmed histologically in all cases.
